  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-PROV-01 orphan chain)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package contains a broken provenance chain: an intermediate ValidationResult node (hemolysis-vr-orphan) is reachable from the Claim via prov:wasDerivedFrom but carries no upstream prov:wasDerivedFrom, prov:wasGeneratedBy, or prov:used edge, and is not marked uofa:isFoundationalEvidence true. Its description states it was 'derived from prior experimental work' without an IRI link, making the dead-end subtle to a quick reviewer.",
